text: before I went to school every day my mom
and dad were like okay Nick it's okay
don't worry about what other people
think of you you're beautiful you're
special and I'm like I don't want to be
special I just want to be what normal
you know the whole idea of what beauty
is you need to be taller shorter thinner
whatever no you're beautiful just the
way you are that's what I want you to
believe today and see that your inner
beauty says much more about anything
about you than your value as far as what
you can do what you're good at what
you're going to be in your career or
anything like that you your soul your
spirit your smile the way you love
people the way you're compassionate the
way you have the ability to listen to
people or communicate whatever it is
just you being you there's never going
to be another you and there has never
been another you you are beautiful
